everywhere ♪

39:51.654 --> 39:55.623
♪ Over there, over there ♪

39:55.658 --> 39:59.961
♪ Send the word,
send the word over there ♪

39:59.996 --> 40:02.330
♪ 'Cause the Yanks are coming ♪

40:02.332 --> 40:04.332
♪ The Yanks are coming ♪

40:04.334 --> 40:07.802
♪ The drums rum-tumming
everywhere... ♪

40:15.645 --> 40:18.229
- Did I wake you?
- No.

40:28.574 --> 40:31.158
Henry shouldn't
have scared you.

40:31.194 --> 40:33.995
I wanted to tell you myself.

40:34.030 --> 40:36.447
He doesn't know
you won't get treatment

40:36.499 --> 40:38.416
because you love the tragedy.

40:38.451 --> 40:40.618
Sally, I've learned

40:40.670 --> 40:43.170
to believe people when
they tell you it's over.

40:43.206 --> 40:47.124
They don't want to say it,
so it's usually the truth.

40:47.176 --> 40:49.377
Henry said you could
have a year.

40:49.429 --> 40:51.462
And what would
that year be like?

40:51.514 --> 40:53.381
I'll be with you.

40:53.383 --> 40:55.049
I won't let you give up.

40:56.302 --> 40:58.102
I know that.

40:59.272 --> 41:02.306
But I watched my mother die.

41:02.358 --> 41:04.275
I won't do that to you.

41:06.279 --> 41:08.396
And I don't want you
to think I'm a quitter.

41:08.448 --> 41:11.232
I fought for plenty in my life.

41:11.234 --> 41:14.201
That's how I know
when it's over.

41:14.237 --> 41:16.487
It's not a weakness.

41:16.539 --> 41:18.205
It's been a gift to me.

41:20.793 --> 41:22.743
To know when to move on.

41:29.085 --> 41:31.919
These are instructions.

41:31.971 --> 41:34.004
Open it the minute
you know I'm gone.

41:36.059 --> 41:38.426
- No.
- Listen to me.

41:38.478 --> 41:41.095
Things happen very quickly
when people die.

41:41.147 --> 41:44.148
Henry's not going to
be able to handle things.

41:49.772 --> 41:51.522
You're going back
to school in the morning.

41:51.574 --> 41:53.741
I don't want you
alarming your brothers.

42:00.583 --> 42:02.366
Go back to sleep.

42:19.469 --> 42:21.852
What the hell?

42:21.888 --> 42:23.437
We want our money.

42:23.473 --> 42:24.855
What?

42:24.891 --> 42:26.190
We know you took the money.

42:26.225 --> 42:29.777
Let me go!
Sharon, what's going on?

42:29.812 --> 42:32.480
Your car was fixed. You
should have been on your way.

42:33.866 --> 42:36.817
Now, I don't know
who the hell you are,

42:36.819 --> 42:39.954
but you've got five Mississippi
to get our money back.

42:39.989 --> 42:41.956
I didn't take your money.

42:42.959 --> 42:44.458
You threw all that money around

42:44.494 --> 42:45.993
'cause you knew
you'd get it back.

42:52.168 --> 42:53.918
I mean business!

42:55.254 --> 42:57.588
You really think I need
your spare change?

43:09.852 --> 43:13.270
Give us the cash and you
can have your car back.

43:13.322 --> 43:16.740
- Probably stolen.
- We'll find out.

43:40.832 --> 43:42.631
My God, what's wrong?

43:42.667 --> 43:44.416
I need to speak with you.

43:44.418 --> 43:45.918
My goodness,
it's 4:00 in the morning.

43:45.920 --> 43:47.503
Is everything all right?

43:53.227 --> 43:55.344
You're scaring me.
Please, what is it?

43:55.396 --> 43:57.596
It's good news.
Catch your breath.

43:57.648 --> 44:01.233
What on earth is going on?

44:01.269 --> 44:03.936
I was offered a job tonight.

44:03.938 --> 44:06.105
Because its origins
were supernatural,

44:06.157 --> 44:08.774
I realized that its
benefits might be as well.

44:09.994 --> 44:12.945
I want you and Tammy
to come with me.

44:12.947 --> 44:16.282
I want you to relocate to
Wichita, pick out a house,

44:16.334 --> 44:19.118
and be my wife
and family again.

44:21.122 --> 44:24.707
Peter, I'm not
dismissing you...

44:25.960 --> 44:28.127
I'm saying with
respect to whatever

44:28.129 --> 44:30.296
is happening in
your eyes right now,

44:30.348 --> 44:33.048
we both know things
can't be undone.

44:33.100 --> 44:35.184
Says who?

44:35.219 --> 44:37.770
We're not even through
half our lives.

44:37.805 --> 44:41.557
And even if we are,
we're entitled to more.

44:41.609 --> 44:43.309
Of what?

44:44.812 --> 44:47.112
Then we're entitled
to something new.

44:49.483 --> 44:51.233
I want to start over.

44:52.870 --> 44:55.154
And I know I can.

44:56.324 --> 44:58.123
I'm not so dumb anymore.

44:58.159 --> 45:01.126
I'm not ignoring the fact that I
could actually lose your love.

45:02.914 --> 45:04.880
You never lost it.

45:04.916 --> 45:07.800
But I will never allow you
to hurt me again.

45:09.637 --> 45:11.637
I love you, too.

45:13.090 --> 45:15.507
I always have.

45:15.509 --> 45:18.143
I've never loved anyone else.

45:18.179 --> 45:19.845
Never.

45:25.736 --> 45:28.270
You think you can come in here

45:28.322 --> 45:30.189
when I'm all disoriented

45:30.241 --> 45:33.025
and say the things I wanted you
to say to me two years ago

45:33.027 --> 45:34.827
and make me run away with you?

45:34.862 --> 45:38.447
I said it to you 10 years
ago and I'll say it again.

45:38.499 --> 45:40.115
I do.

45:44.038 --> 45:46.205
Wichita is beautiful.

45:46.207 --> 45:48.340
And wholesome.

45:48.376 --> 45:51.210
And not the city
and not Cos Cob.

45:51.262 --> 45:53.595
And you'll have a plane
to use at your disposal.

45:53.631 --> 45:54.847
We will.

45:54.882 --> 45:58.550
To pick up and go anywhere
anytime we want.

45:58.552 --> 46:01.387
Like driving to Montauk.

46:01.439 --> 46:03.856
I want to go
everywhere with you.

46:09.447 --> 46:12.448
Say yes with your voice,
not just your eyes.

46:14.485 --> 46:16.235
Oh!

46:34.255 --> 46:36.422
How will I explain
this to Tammy?

46:38.142 --> 46:42.177
Tell her her birthday
wish came true.

46:48.602 --> 46:51.020
I'm gonna go.

46:51.072 --> 46:53.939
And we're gonna have
dinner on Saturday night.

46:53.991 --> 46:55.858
The three of us.

46:56.944 --> 46:58.861
Like it was the first time.

47:15.763 --> 47:17.546
Good morning.

47:45.126 --> 47:47.159
This one's on the house.

47:49.997 --> 47:52.581
What do you want to know?
You want to know what I told them?

47:52.633 --> 47:54.416
I'm just being
a good citizen, man.

47:54.468 --> 47:57.169
You don't know anything about me.
I could kill you right now.

47:57.171 --> 47:58.971
You took that money
and you set me up.

48:00.424 --> 48:02.224
I don't know what
you're talking about.

48:02.259 --> 48:04.176
You have shitty instincts
for a con man.

48:05.646 --> 48:07.346
You're lucky you feel guilty.

48:07.398 --> 48:08.931
That's the one difference between
you and those animals right now.

48:08.983 --> 48:11.517
I don't feel guilty
taking that drunk's money.

48:11.569 --> 48:13.185
He burned his own house down.

48:13.187 --> 48:15.821
He doesn't deserve a pot to
piss in, let alone 500 bucks.

48:15.856 --> 48:17.322
You're gonna get me that money,

48:17.358 --> 48:19.108
pack your bag,
and get out of town.

48:19.160 --> 48:21.860
I can't leave
without that money.

48:21.862 --> 48:24.413
I know you think
you know how to hustle,

48:24.448 --> 48:27.533
but this is a big crime,
stealing these people's money.

48:27.535 --> 48:30.953
If you keep it, you'll have
to become somebody else.

48:31.005 --> 48:33.288
And it's not
what you think it is.

48:35.342 --> 48:38.260
You cannot get off
on that foot in this life.

48:38.295 --> 48:40.095
What do you care?

48:40.131 --> 48:42.381
You got money.
I know you got money.

48:42.433 --> 48:44.850
I cleaned your room
and didn't take nothing.

48:44.885 --> 48:46.051
Anything.

48:46.053 --> 48:47.553
You think this town is bad now?

48:47.555 --> 48:49.471
Wait until you can
never come back.

48:49.523 --> 48:51.306
Can I go?

48:51.358 --> 48:53.225
Go get the money.

49:25.893 --> 49:27.759
I'm not paying for the room.

49:38.439 --> 49:40.606
Could you drop me off
at the bus stop?

49:44.828 --> 49:46.111
Get in.

49:59.627 --> 50:01.677
I'm off.

50:01.712 --> 50:04.046
- Where are you going?
- I have class.

50:05.382 --> 50:07.015
Why are you doing that?

50:07.051 --> 50:09.935
Why was I ever doing it?

